The method of Sestak [25] and Lichtenthaler [26] was followed with minor modifications for total chlorophyll and carotenoids determination. Shoot tissue (100 mg) from chromium (VI)-treated seedlings was crushed and homogenized with a pestle using ice-cold acetone in a mortar. The total volume was adjusted to 5 ml with ice-cold acetone (SRL, India). The mixture was then centrifuged using a cold centrifuge machine (4 °C) for 10 min at 7728×g. The supernatant was collected and absorbance was measured according to the following equations:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
